    {
      "id": "sybil_8_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_8",
      "description": "Offered is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46) powered by the S54B32 3.2L I6 engine featuring individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double-VANOS timing. This example is equipped with the Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and a factory-spec variable M differential lock. Preventative maintenance is up to date, including rod bearing replacement and a reinforced rear subframe to ensure structural rigidity under lateral load. The suspension retains its original geometry with refreshed bushings for precise turn-in. While showing honest wear consistent with a well-maintained driver's car, the powertrain delivers linear torque and maintains excellent compression across all cylinders. A technically sound platform for the purist who values mechanical integrity.",
